



To Mr BelfourPartr to Colo. Hunter\Hampton/Sir
[Winchester, 16 May 1755]



If Colo. \Hunter/ shd be from home, I hope you will open this \my/ Lett. to see \to him and attend to/ the Contents1that you may dispatch a messenger to him \in that case/ immediately to prevent his trouble in getting the 10 or 15 Thd Pounds mentd \required/ in a former Letter2but repair immediately to Wmsburg with the 4,000 which is all I am to receive at prest. I am Sir yours &ca.

Winchester 16th May 1755

